{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place vanilla pod, sugar and lime zest in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","With a sharp knife, peel pineapple, cut vertically in 4-6 wedges (depending on size of pineapple) and remove core. Cut each wedge in 3-5 mm slices and place on a sheet of baking paper or heat-resistant cling film, keeping slices aligned to preserve the wedge shape. Drizzle pineapple with rum (if using), sprinkle with reserved sugar mixture and close the parcels. Arrange parcels in Varoma dish and tray then leave to marinate for 20-30 minutes.","Place water in mixing bowl, set covered Varoma into position and steam <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma. To serve, carefully open parcels, arrange pineapple wedges on dessert plates, sprinkle with chopped mint leaves and serve warm or cold."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["¼ - ½ vanilla pod, to taste, halved lengthways","50 g brown sugar","1 lime, finely grated zest only","1 pineapple (see tip)","30 - 40 g rum              (optional)","400 g water","4 fresh mint leaves, finely chopped"]}],"id":"r150931","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-WLZw05EBWkY\/XZWefsuLpeI\/AAAAAAAAe1E\/OsSUN_KKMOUCofByQpZH5G-_HPOdWVGEwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_aRD795qDcd_MoaV6.png","title":"Pineapple Parcels","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"35 g","calories":"739 kJ \/ 177 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper or heat-resistant cling film","hintsAndTricks":["This simple preparation method enhances the natural flavour of fresh pineapple and makes a lovely, light dessert that can be served hot or cold.","For 4 portions, the pineapple should weigh <nobr>650-800 g<\/nobr> peeled (approx. <nobr>1500-1700 g<\/nobr> unpeeled).<br>- Serve warm with a scoop of lime sorbet or ice cream of your choice (e.g. vanilla, coconut, rum and raisin).<br>- After peeling the pineapple you can remove any remaining 'eyes' with a melon baller or the tip of a vegetable peeler.","<br>- Replace lime zest with orange or lemon zest, and brown sugar with coconut sugar."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h","4 portions"]}